Preconditions:
- The input matrix is a 2D array of distinct numbers.
- The matrix has at least one row and one column.
- The number of rows and columns in the matrix is between 1 and 50 (inclusive).
- The values in the matrix are between 1 and 10^5 (inclusive).

Postconditions:
- The method returns a list of lucky numbers.
- The lucky numbers are the minimum elements in their respective rows and the maximum elements in their respective columns.
- The lucky numbers are distinct and appear in any order.